-- Rwanda's Economy Grew 7.4% in 2010, to Grow 7% This Year, Minister Says
-- B y   D a v i d   M a l i n g h a   D o y a
-- 2011-02-02T14:09:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-02/rwanda-s-economy-grew-7-4-in-2010-to-grow-7-this-year-minister-says.html
Rwanda’s economy expanded 7.4 percent
in 2010 and is estimated to grow by 7 percent this year, Finance
Minister John Rwangombwa said.  The agriculture industry grew by 7.2 percent according to
provisional data, Rwangombwa told reporters today in the
capital, Kigali.  The  International Monetary Fund  on Jan. 11 forecast 6.5
percent growth in 2011 for the the East African nation’s
economy, with inflation expected to remain ‘low.’ Annual
inflation was 0.23 percent in December, according to the
country’s statistics agency.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Malingha Doya in Kigali at 
 dmalingha@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  